comment._content: In May 1891 the Dyer's Buildings were advertised for mortgagee sale, and presumably named for Mr Dyer who had a grocery store there. Fascinating full details of the buildings in the SMH of 27/5/1891 p.10, column 6, first item "By order of the mortgagees ..." - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/13825800 Probably built 1890
